                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13584996" author="mumrah" created="Sat, 23 Feb 2013 03:55:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Isn&apos;t there a more &quot;Scala-y&quot; way to do this sort of thing? Perhaps if ApiUtils#readShortString returned Option(String) instead of just String? OffsetMetadataAndError would need to do the same thing. This would be a large refactoring due to the ubiquity of readShortString&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13585484" author="nehanarkhede" created="Sun, 24 Feb 2013 20:27:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is this a patch on 0.8 since it doesn&apos;t apply cleanly, please can you rebase ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13585535" author="mumrah" created="Sun, 24 Feb 2013 23:36:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, my mistake. Should be applied to trunk (the new commit/fetch offset APIs are not on 0.8)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13585567" author="nehanarkhede" created="Mon, 25 Feb 2013 02:11:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah, that was my bad. +1 on your patch, looks good.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
